00:27:49.150 --> 00:27:53.740
second, driving games
discovery; and third improving

00:27:53.740 --> 00:27:55.580
monetization.

00:27:55.580 --> 00:27:58.480
So let's dive in
with star listings.

00:27:58.480 --> 00:28:01.960
Back in 2015, we launched
store listing experiments,

00:28:01.960 --> 00:28:04.210
enabling you to A/B
test different variants

00:28:04.210 --> 00:28:06.460
of your store listings page.

00:28:06.460 --> 00:28:08.770
We were excited to see how
quickly developers adopted

00:28:08.770 --> 00:28:12.340
this feature to test everything
from icons and screenshots

00:28:12.340 --> 00:28:14.035
to titles and descriptions.

00:28:14.035 --> 00:28:16.750
And we were even more
surprised to see developers

00:28:16.750 --> 00:28:19.480
hiring dedicated teams
to specifically focus

00:28:19.480 --> 00:28:21.790
on apps or optimization.

00:28:21.790 --> 00:28:23.890
Your enthusiasm and
feedback in this area

00:28:23.890 --> 00:28:25.240
led us to invest more.

00:28:25.240 --> 00:28:29.725
And so recently, we launched
custom listing pages.

00:28:29.725 --> 00:28:31.600
With this capability,
you now have the option

00:28:31.600 --> 00:28:33.220
of having multiple
unique listing

00:28:33.220 --> 00:28:35.650
pages in production targetable
to different audiences

00:28:35.650 --> 00:28:36.220
like country.

00:28:39.400 --> 00:28:42.280
Over the holidays,
Refi, a developer

00:28:42.280 --> 00:28:44.710
from India with a cookbook
app, leveraged this country

00:28:44.710 --> 00:28:47.170
targeting capability to
tune their featured graphic

00:28:47.170 --> 00:28:52.900
by country, resulting in a 17%
increase to install conversion.

00:28:52.900 --> 00:28:54.370
And today, I'm
excited to announce

00:28:54.370 --> 00:28:56.912
that we're taking this a step
further with a new early access

00:28:56.912 --> 00:28:58.300
program.

00:28:58.300 --> 00:29:01.210
Custom listings
by install state--

00:29:01.210 --> 00:29:02.830
with this capability,
you now can

00:29:02.830 --> 00:29:05.390
target three new audiences--

00:29:05.390 --> 00:29:07.630
users who have never
installed your app,

00:29:07.630 --> 00:29:09.760
users who've
uninstalled your app,

00:29:09.760 --> 00:29:13.128
and users who currently
have your app installed.

00:29:13.128 --> 00:29:14.170
We're excited about this.

00:29:14.170 --> 00:29:15.940
And if you're interested
in trying it out,

00:29:15.940 --> 00:29:16.732
check out the link.

00:29:19.030 --> 00:29:21.490
Also at GDC this
year, we announced

00:29:21.490 --> 00:29:25.420
the general availability
of preregistration support.

00:29:25.420 --> 00:29:26.950
With preregistration,
you can now

00:29:26.950 --> 00:29:29.470
build hype and excitement
around your app or game

00:29:29.470 --> 00:29:31.690
prior to launch.

00:29:31.690 --> 00:29:34.150
Today, we're adding two
new features onto this.

00:29:34.150 --> 00:29:37.000
First, you can now have
custom listings pages

00:29:37.000 --> 00:29:39.460
for the preregistration stage.

00:29:39.460 --> 00:29:41.500
And second, we're
adding a new feature

00:29:41.500 --> 00:29:44.020
we call pre registration
rewards, which

00:29:44.020 --> 00:29:46.130
now enables you to give
users who preregister

00:29:46.130 --> 00:29:49.300
a special in-app gift.

00:29:49.300 --> 00:29:52.080
Nexon the creator
of the game "Faith,"

00:29:52.080 --> 00:29:54.310
leverages this
capability and saw

00:29:54.310 --> 00:29:56.080
that users who
were given a reward

00:29:56.080 --> 00:30:00.130
were 20% more likely to
be retained at day 30.

00:30:00.130 --> 00:30:02.020
They also saw a
significant improvement

00:30:02.020 --> 00:30:04.920
in conversion between
people who preregistered

00:30:04.920 --> 00:30:08.735
and users who actually installed
the app and it was released.

00:30:08.735 --> 00:30:10.610
We're really excited
about these capabilities

00:30:10.610 --> 00:30:13.765
and see how you use them to
tune your conversion funnel.

00:30:13.765 --> 00:30:15.890
As always, please let us
know if you have feedback.

00:30:15.890 --> 00:30:18.437
We'd like not improve.

00:30:18.437 --> 00:30:21.020
And one last thing while we're
on the topic of that conversion

00:30:21.020 --> 00:30:25.940
funnel, I want to make a
quick plug for app icons.

00:30:25.940 --> 00:30:28.850
We announced the new icon
spec earlier this year,

00:30:28.850 --> 00:30:32.152
